commText: Sai Sudharsan and Shubman Gill are at the crease. Sai Sudharsan is on strike. Santner will open the attack
Santner to Sai Sudharsan, 2 runs, on the shorter side, Sai Sudharsan drags it through backward square leg for a couple of runs
Santner to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, hint of swing around off, Sai Sudharsan clips it towards the leg-side for a single
More support for CSK than GT as chants of 'CSK, CSK,' engulf the stadium..

Santner to Shubman Gill, FOUR, Shubman Gill gets off the mark with a boundary. Flatter through the air on off, keeps straight as Shubman Gill cuts it past the fielder at point for the first boundary of the match. Santer not happy with the fielder's effort
Santner to Shubman Gill, no run, on a length around off, Shubman Gill knocks it back to the bowler
Santner to Shubman Gill, SIX, first maximum of the match. Shubman Gill shimmies down the wicket and launches it over long-on for half-a-dozen
Santner to Shubman Gill, 1 run, a productive opening over for GT. 14 runs from it. This was a tad short as Shubman Gill punched it to long-off for a single
Tushar Deshpande, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Tushar Deshpande to Shubman Gill, wide, Tushar Deshpande starts off with a wide one down the leg-side. Gill was trying to flick it away but couldn't connect
Tushar Deshpande to Shubman Gill, no run, on a length around off, good line by Tushar Deshpande as Shubman Gill defends it from within the crease

Tushar Deshpande to Shubman Gill, 1 run, short of a length around middle and leg, nips back in as Shubman Gill nudges it off an inside edge to the leg-side, a quick run taken. Looks like he got hit after that inside edge and the physio was quick to charge on to the field, Gill looks fine though

Thakur to Sai Sudharsan, SIX, beautiful. This was pitched up by the bowler on off, Sai Sudharsan goes down on his knee and lofts it over wide long-off for an elegant maximum

Tushar Deshpande to Sai Sudharsan, no run, slower delivery outside off, Sai Sudharsan leaves it alone. Was it a wide? Gill and Sudharsan have a word but don't opt for the review. Guess it was just inside the tramline
Tushar Deshpande to Sai Sudharsan, 2 runs, short of a length around off, Sai Sudharsan whips it through mid-wicket for a couple of runs. Good running between the wickets
Tushar Deshpande to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, back of a length on middle and leg, Sai Sudharsan nudges it through backward square leg for a single
Thakur to Sai Sudharsan, no run, 136 clicks, short of a length on middle and leg, Sai Sudharsan whips it to mid-wicket on the bounce
Thakur to Sai Sudharsan, no run, deft touch but straight to the fielder. Short of a length outside off, Sai Sudharsan opens the bat face and steers it to short third man
Thakur to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, on a length around middle as Sai Sudharsan clips it through square leg for a single
Thakur to Shubman Gill, no run, pitched up by the bowler as Shubman Gill drives it to mid-on
Thakur to Shubman Gill, 1 run, on a length around off, Shubman Gill steers it to point for a single
Thakur to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, width on offer as Sai Sudharsan cuts this through point for a single
Simarjeet Singh, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Simarjeet Singh to Sai Sudharsan, no run, short and wide outside off, Sai cuts it straight to the fielder at point

Simarjeet Singh to Sai Sudharsan, 2 runs, slight width on offer as Sudharsan cuts it through point for a couple of runs. The throw came in at the keeper's end who disloged the bails but Sai Sudharsan was in
Simarjeet Singh to Sai Sudharsan, 2 runs, 50-run stand up! On the shorter side as Sai Sudharsan works it through backward square leg for a couple of runs
Simarjeet Singh to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, short of a length around middle and leg, nudged to mid-on for a single
Simarjeet Singh to Shubman Gill, SIX, stand and deliver. Stays put and spanks this back of a length delivery over long-on for half-a-dozen does Shubman Gill. More like a baseball swing

Powerplay summary -- Gill bats positively and gets off to a quick start -- Santner taken for 14 in the first over -- Sai off to a steady start -- Not much movement with the new ball for CSK -- Pitch looks good for batting
Ravindra Jadeja, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack

Jadeja to Shubman Gill, FOUR, Shubman Gill greets Jadeja with a boundary. This was a touch short and Shubman Gill picks the length early, drags it through mid-wicket and splits the two fielders in the deep
STAT: 58/0 is the second highest powerplay score for GT this season and highest batting first.
Jadeja to Shubman Gill, 1 run, quicker through the air on leg, Shubman Gill nudges it into the leg-side for a single
Jadeja to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, flatter delivery on leg, Sai Sudharsan sweeps it through backward square leg for a single
Jadeja to Shubman Gill, 1 run, darted on off, Shubman Gill taps it with soft hands to mid-off and scampers across

Has a wayward throw at the bowler's end as Rachin Ravindra who was backing up makes a mess of it. The ball goes through him and those are four bonus runs
Jadeja to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, another expensive over. This was darted by Jadeja and Sai Sudharsan nudges it towards mid-on for a quick run again

Daryl Mitchell, right-arm medium, comes into the attack

Mitchell to Shubman Gill, 1 run, on a length around middle and leg, clipped to long-on by Shubman Gill for a single
Mitchell to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, on the shorter side as Sai Sudharsan pulls it to wide long-on for a single

Mitchell to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, short of a length around off, whipped through long-on for a single

Strategic timeout! GT off to a solid start as both the openers are playing some aggressive cricket. CSK in search of a wicket. The pitch looks a really good one for batting and CSK bat almost till no.10 tonight.. It's important for the Titans to score as many runs as they can..

Mitchell to Shubman Gill, FOUR, drilled down the ground. Pitched up by the bowler and Shubman Gill has nailed the drive straight past Mitchell. No chance of stopping that, couldn't have played it any straighter

Mitchell to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, 100-run stand up. Looks to play the scoop shot, doesn't middle it though. Just a single as the ball drops in front of short fine leg

Mitchell to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, that was all about timing. Short of a length around off, Sai Sudharsan stays put and punches it right past the bowler, the timing was supreme. The fielders from mid-off and long-on - both couldn't get there

Gaikwad having a word with Simarjeet, fine leg comes in, mid-off moves to long-off
Simarjeet Singh to Shubman Gill, no run, yorker length delivery on off, Shubman Gill squeezes it back to the bowler
Simarjeet Singh to Shubman Gill, 1 run, yorker length delivery on off, Shubman Gill squeezes it towards cover for a single

Santner to Sai Sudharsan, SIX, moves into the 90s. Tossed up delivery, right into the slot and Sai Sudharsan has smoked this over deep mid-wicket for half-a-dozen more. GT going strong at 160/0 in 13. 250 on the cards?

This is a brilliant assault from GT. The lower ranked teams will be jumping in joy that GT are absolutely piling on the runs and CSK's NRR takes a big dent too. Having said that, this seems to be a belter, so you never know
Mitchell to Shubman Gill, no run, wide yorker, Gill lets it go hoping for a wide but it's a fair delivery

Mitchell to Shubman Gill, SIX, mis-hit, mis-hit.. Ohhh Tushar Deshpande has dropped it. Camera pans to Mitchell, he takes a pause and absolutely fumes. That was a schoolboy error from Deshpande. Slot delivery that Gill mistimed as he targetted the long-off boundary. Tushar had a lot of space to go back and take it easily. You wonder if Ruturaj could have used Santner more. Yes there's not much in for spin, but Santner is a class act at varying speeds and can outdo batters in flight. The worry of Sai taking him on seems to be playing a bigger role on the captains mind, but his other choices are anyway going 15+ easily.

Tushar Deshpande to Shubman Gill, wide, tries the wide yorker, but too wide

Shahrukh Khan run out (Ravindra/Simarjeet Singh) 2(3)

21:19 Local Time, 15:49 GMT, 21:19 IST: 231 is a very good score, but you to say CSK did brilliantly well to only concede 41 runs off the last five overs. Sai and Gill batted was just outstanding, but interestingly, none of the GT batters, including both the set batters couldn't middle the ball at all for the last few balls. There's no real sight of dew. Is it tougher to bat against the older ball? We will have to wait and see. Gill was on a mission - to shut the negativity around him and he put on a mega show. Sai wasn't going great for most parts of PP but picked up big time and matched his captain shot for shot. Those two put on a record stand and made the bowling look absolutely ordinary. Ruturaj didn't believe much in spinners and used up his part-timer and rotated between other bowlers. Didn't help that Gill was put down by Deshpande. Shardul and Deshpande bowled brilliant to keep this around 230. But Chennai did feel the absence of Pathirana and Fizz. Both Gill and Sai made the pitch look flat. If it stays the same, CSK will fancy their chances too. Gill did say he didn't expect dew tonight. If that's the case then it's advantage GT.

Sai Sudharsan: It was a great innings, very happy to execute (the plans) in this game. I think the wicket is great to bat on. Mixing it well and going wide will be good (for our bowlers.) It was sticking into the surface initially but the wicket got better. The slower balls are gripping more. It was great to watch Gill bat, learning things from him. I don't think it (playing well against CSK) is relatable to Chennai, just trying to give my best in every game. This knock was a special one for me.
